  "prompt": "In Hurt Locker, how come Guy Pearce's character died due to the explosion despite all the padding and being outside the kill zone?",
  "response": "In \"The Hurt Locker,\" Staff Sergeant Matt Thompson, played by Guy Pearce, dies in the opening scene despite wearing a bomb suit because of the scale and power of the explosion. Bomb suits are designed to protect against shrapnel and debris rather than the extreme concussive force of large blasts. Even outside what is typically considered the kill zone, the sheer force of a large enough explosion can cause fatal internal injuries, including traumatic brain injuries caused by the pressure wave. Additionally, the suit cannot fully protect against other factors, such as the heat of the explosion or structural collapse. This scene highlights the inherent risks and unpredictabilities of bomb disposal work, regardless of precautions taken.",
